body:
Probably not as the publicly available packages are *not* built with `--enable_external_custom_op_schemas` by default.

@satyajandhyala @SherlockNoMad  and I discussed this a couple times. Maybe we should enable this by default soon to allow extensions without builds from scratch
Is it for ORT training or inferencing?

> Is it for ORT training or inferencing?

good point. my answer was related to training, only

> > Is it for ORT training or inferencing?
> 
> good point. my answer was related to training, only

Why training or inferencing matters?

> Is is possible to develop custom c++ op (with cuda support) without building onnxruntime, just like developing the custom op for TensorFlow that we only need to include header files and link the libtensorflow_framework.so ?

Yes for inferencing. See https://onnxruntime.ai/docs/reference/operators/add-custom-op.html#cuda-custom-ops
@pranavsharma  Thank you, I will try it.

> Why training or inferencing matters?

To find the best person to answer your question.  I wonder if you were asking something about ORT training module.
